        "text_tzFHae": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p></p><h4><strong>Memory Foam</strong></h4><p>Memory foam mattresses contour to your body, providing excellent pressure relief. They are ideal for side sleepers or those with joint pain.</p><ul><li><strong>Pros</strong>: Great for motion isolation, excellent for side sleepers.</li><li><strong>Cons</strong>: May retain heat, less responsive.</li></ul><p>Explore our <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/collections/memory-foam-mattresses\">memory foam mattresses</a>.</p><h4><strong>Innerspring</strong></h4><p>Innerspring mattresses use a coil system for support and tend to be more breathable than foam options.</p><ul><li><strong>Pros</strong>: Affordable, provides strong support.</li><li><strong>Cons</strong>: Less pressure relief, may transfer motion.</li></ul><p>Check out our <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/collections/innerspring-mattresses\">innerspring collection</a>.</p><h4><strong>Hybrid</strong></h4><p>Hybrids combine innerspring coils with foam or latex layers, offering the best of both worlds.</p><ul><li><strong>Pros</strong>: Excellent balance of support and comfort.</li><li><strong>Cons</strong>: Typically more expensive.</li></ul><p>Browse our <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/collections/hybrid-mattresses\">hybrid mattresses</a>.</p><h4><strong>Latex</strong></h4><p>Natural and synthetic latex mattresses are durable and eco-friendly and biodegradable. They offer firm support without sacrificing comfort. Latex mattresses are an excellent option for eco-conscious shoppers due to their sustainability and natural materials.</p><ul><li><strong>Pros</strong>: Long-lasting, hypoallergenic, naturally antibacterial.</li><li><strong>Cons</strong>: Can be pricey.</li></ul><p>Discover our <a href=\"https://mattressville.ca/collections/latex-mattresses\">latex mattresses</a>.</p><h4><strong>Pocket Coil</strong></h4><p> A specialized type of innerspring where each coil is individually wrapped in fabric.</p><ul><li><strong>Pros:</strong> Better motion isolation than open-coil innerspring, offers more targeted support.</li><li><strong>Cons:</strong> Often pricier than traditional innerspring, can be heavier, and coils may still wear down over time.<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>Step 2: Identify Your Sleeping Position</strong></h3><p></p>"
          }
        }
      },
